Title : I Believe in You (Frank Loesser song)
Text : "'''I Believe in You'''" is a 1961 song written by [[Frank Loesser]] for his musical ''[[How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying (musical)|How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying]]'', where it was introduced by [[Robert Morse]].<ref name="Block2009">{{cite book|author=Geoffrey Block|title=Enchanted Evenings: The Broadway Musical from 'Show Boat' to Sondheim and Lloyd Webber|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hH3fGlu05dYC&pg=PT256|date=2 October 2009|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-988882-5|pages=256–}}</ref> The protagonist of the musical, J. Pierrepont Finch, sings the song to himself in the mirror while shaving.<ref name="Hischak2008">{{cite book|author=Thomas S. Hischak|title=The Oxford Companion to the American Musical: Theatre, Film, and Television|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XbBz3C4Gr0EC&pg=PA353|date=2 June 2008|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-533533-0|pages=353–}}</ref> In the [[How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying (film)|movie version]], Rosemary (played by [[Michele Lee]]) also sings it to Pierrepont (again played by Morse).

==Notable recordings==
* [[Anita O'Day]] - included in her album ''[[Time for 2]]'' (1962)
* [[Peggy Lee]] - [[Sugar 'n' Spice (Peggy Lee album)|Sugar ‘n’ Spice]] ‘’ (1962)
* [[Jack Jones (singer)|Jack Jones]] - for his album ''She Loves Me'' (1963).<ref>{{cite web |title=Discogs.com |url=https://www.discogs.com/Jack-Jones-With-Jack-Elliott-And-His-Orchestra-She-Loves-Me/master/723096 |website=Discogs.com |accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref>
* [[Sarah Vaughan]] - ''[[The Explosive Side of Sarah Vaughan]]'' (1963)
* [[Nancy Wilson (jazz singer)|Nancy Wilson]] - ''[[Broadway – My Way]]'' (1964)
* [[Frank Sinatra]] and [[Count Basie]] - ''[[It Might As Well Be Swing]]'' (1964)
* [[Shirley Bassey]] - ''[[Shirley Stops the Shows]]'' (1965)
* [[Bobby Darin]] - ''[[In a Broadway Bag (Mame)]]'' (1966)
* [[Dionne Warwick]] - ''[[On Stage and in the Movies]]'' (1967)
* [[Steve Lawrence]] and [[Eydie Gorme]] - ''Together on Broadway'' (1967).<ref>{{cite web |title=Discogs.com |url=https://www.discogs.com/Steve-Eydie-Together-On-Broadway/master/663993 |website=Discogs.com |accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref>
* [[Jo Stafford]] & [[Warren Covington]] - recorded in 1969 for a Reader's Digest set.<ref>{{cite web |title=Big Band Library |url=http://www.bigbandlibrary.com/readersdigestsessions.html |website=bigbandlibrary.com |accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref>

